36/* Id */
37
38#ifndef __GETARG_H__
39#define __GETARG_H__
40
41#include <stddef.h>
42
43#ifndef ROKEN_LIB_FUNCTION
44#ifdef _WIN32
45#define ROKEN_LIB_FUNCTION
46#define ROKEN_LIB_CALL __cdecl
47#else
48#define ROKEN_LIB_FUNCTION
49#define ROKEN_LIB_CALL
50#endif
51#endif
52
53struct getargs{
54 const char *long_name;
55 char short_name;
56 enum { arg_integer,
57 arg_string,
58 arg_flag,
59 arg_negative_flag,
60 arg_strings,
61 arg_double,
62 arg_collect,
63 arg_counter
64 } type;
65 void *value;
66 const char *help;
67 const char *arg_help;
68};
69
70enum {
71 ARG_ERR_NO_MATCH = 1,
72 ARG_ERR_BAD_ARG,
73 ARG_ERR_NO_ARG
74};
75
76typedef struct getarg_strings {
77 int num_strings;
78 char **strings;
79} getarg_strings;
80
81typedef int (*getarg_collect_func)(int short_opt,
82 int argc,
83 char **argv,
84 int *goptind,
85 int *goptarg,
86 void *data);
87
88typedef struct getarg_collect_info {
89 getarg_collect_func func;
90 void *data;
91} getarg_collect_info;
92
93ROKEN_LIB_FUNCTION int ROKEN_LIB_CALL
94getarg(struct getargs *args, size_t num_args,
95 int argc, char **argv, int *goptind);
96
97ROKEN_LIB_FUNCTION void ROKEN_LIB_CALL
98arg_printusage (struct getargs *args,
99 size_t num_args,
100 const char *progname,
101 const char *extra_string);
102
103ROKEN_LIB_FUNCTION void ROKEN_LIB_CALL
104arg_printusage_i18n (struct getargs *args,
105 size_t num_args,
106 const char *usage,
107 const char *progname,
108 const char *extra_string,
109 char *(*i18n)(const char *));
110
111ROKEN_LIB_FUNCTION void ROKEN_LIB_CALL
112free_getarg_strings (getarg_strings *);
113
114#endif /* __GETARG_H__ */
115
